      • loadToKbUnlessKbContentExists

        public List<String> loadToKbUnlessKbContentExists(String... namesOrIds)
                                           throws com.cyc.kb.exception.KbException
        Loads the contents of the KE text file into the KB, but only if all terms and/or assertions in namesOrIds do not already exist in the KB. This method returns all of the names/IDs from that list which it has found in the KB; if empty, it will have attempted to load the KE text file.
        Parameters:
        namesOrIds - names or IDs of all terms/assertions which must not already exist in the KB
        Returns:
        list of all terms/assertions that already exist in the KB
        Throws:
        com.cyc.kb.exception.KbException
        See Also:
        loadToKb(), loadKeTextString(java.lang.String)
